replies.text:
@Greg Mark You're not wrong about the console limitations of showing a full image of the entire world. That doesn't sound very practical.

I would not say tiles were used "primarily" to save memory though. Tiles, being data points in 2D arrays, are just a structured way of tracking space in games. Every single room in many text-based games are technically tiles, and the player's position in it's world is tracked using 2D arrays. It's just the most practical approach.

In terms of saving memory, that would be the way tile sets are utilized, which are the sprites.
